So today I pretty much quit therapy, because the woman doesn't even listen when I talk. I was telling her how I could have said certain things to Andy that would have gotten us into a petty argument, but I kept my mouth shut because I'd rather be pleasant, and no matter what I've never liked doing anything to upset him. Then she said, "Do you feel the same way with your father?" And I was like, "well I wasn't done talking about Andy..." and she just kept talking about my dad. When I told her I wanted to talk about different relationships and not just my father, she said that I wasn't addressing issues and I was being weak and hiding from my problems and creating 'more depression' which just pissed me off. So I decided I'm not going to talk to someone who won't listen to me. We discussed my father for three months. I'm sorry if I want to talk about my ex-boyfriend for a day.

*sigh* I've been feeling worse going to therapy then I have when I'm outside of the place. Not because it's where I have to face my demons, but because she creates them for me.

Ken won Jeopardy again, and I knew the Final Jeopardy question so I felt really smart :D Yay for knowing stuff about Bill Clinton :D
